                <head>Wednesbury Local Board of Health</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wednesbury Local Board of Health</hi>, <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am instructed by the above Board of Health, as
                    representing the inhabitants of the town of Wednesbury, containing upwards of
                    23,000 population, to forward to you a copy of a resolution passed at the last
                    meeting of the board held on the 1st of this present month of May, as
                    follows:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That this board expresses its detestation of
                    the assassination of President Lincoln, and of the brutal attack upon Secretary
                    Seward, and also its sympathy with the people of the United States of America
                    upon the great and irreparable loss they have sustained thereby. I am, sir, your
                    most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM TANLY BAILEY,</signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Clerk of the Board</hi>.</closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles F. Adams</hi>, Esq., <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Ambassador of the United States, London</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
